#### `extensions/pulseboard/src/client.ts`
Fictional PulseBoard WebSocket client. No real npm dependency — uses the built-in `WebSocket` global (Node 22+).

Key exported types/functions:
```ts
export type PulseboardClientOptions = {
  apiUrl: string;
  apiToken: string;
  userId: string;
  boards?: string[];
  abortSignal?: AbortSignal;
  connectTimeoutMs?: number;
  onMessage?: (msg: PulseboardInboundMessage) => void | Promise<void>;
  onError?: (err: Error) => void;
  onDisconnect?: () => void;
};

export type PulseboardClient = {
  sendMessage(target: string, text: string): void;
  isReady(): boolean;
  disconnect(reason?: string): void;
  readonly userId: string;
};

export async function connectPulseboardClient(
  opts: PulseboardClientOptions
): Promise<PulseboardClient>
```

Implementation sketch:
- Opens `new WebSocket(opts.apiUrl)`
- On `open`: sends JSON auth frame `{ type: "auth", token: opts.apiToken, userId: opts.userId }`
- On `message`: parses JSON frames of shape `{ type: "message", from, target, body, ts, msgId }`, determines `isBoard` via `isBoardTarget(target)`, calls `onMessage`
- `sendMessage(target, text)`: sends `{ type: "send", to: target, body: text }`
- Handles abort signal → `disconnect()`
- Probe path: separate `connectForProbe()` that resolves after auth ACK, then disconnects

#### `extensions/pulseboard/src/probe.ts`
```ts
export async function probePulseboard(
  cfg: CoreConfig,
  opts?: { accountId?: string; timeoutMs?: number }
): Promise<PulseboardProbe>
```
- Resolves account; returns `ok: false, error: "missing apiToken or userId"` if unconfigured
- Calls `connectPulseboardClient({ ..., connectTimeoutMs })`, measures latency, disconnects
- Returns `{ ok: true, apiUrl, userId, latencyMs }` on success or `{ ok: false, error }` on failure

